definition.value: An alkenyl alcohol with a structure based on a C8 unbranched chain with the hydroxy group at C-2 and unsaturation at C-1-C-2. It is a major volatile compound present in many mushrooms and fungi.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is tridecane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1.
An 11-HETE in which the chiral centre at position 11 has R-configuration.
An EET obtained by formal epoxidation of the 11,12-double bond of arachidonic acid.
A trihydroxyicosatrienoic acid that is (5Z,8Z,12E)-icosatrienoic acid in which the three hydroxy groups are located at positions 11, 14 and 15.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is testosterone carrying an additional oxo substituent at position 11.
A HETE having a (12R)-hydroxy group and (5Z)-, (8Z)-, (10E)- and (14Z)-double bonds.
A HPETE that is (5Z,8Z,10E,12R,14Z)-icosa-5,8,10,14-tetraenoic acid with the hydroperoxy group located at position 12 (the R-enantiomer).
A HETE having a (12S)-hydroxy group and (5Z)-, (8Z)-, (10E)- and (14Z)-double bonds.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-carfentrazone. A protoporphyrinogen oxidase inhibitor, it is used (generally as the corresponding ethyl ester, carfentrazone-ethyl) to control broad-leafed weeds in potatoes and cereal crops.
An oxoicosatetraenoic acid having a 12-oxo group; and (5Z)-, (8Z), (10E)- and (14Z)-double bonds.
An HODE (hydroxyoctadecadienoic acid) in which the double bonds are at positions 9 and 11 (E and Z geometry, respectively) and the hydroxy group is at position 13 (with S-configuration).
An EET obtained by formal epoxidation of the 14,15-double bond of arachidonic acid.
A prostaglandin J derivative comprising prostaglandin J2 lacking the 15-hydroxy group and having C=C double bonds at the 12- and 14-positions.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-carfentrazone-ethylcarfentrazone-ethyl. A proherbicide for the herbicide carfentrazone (by hydrolysis of the ester group to the corresponding acid), it is used to control broad-leafed weeds in potatoes and cereal crops.
An androstanoid that is testosterone substituted by a alpha-hydroxy group at position 15. A natural product found in Daphnia magna exposed to the biocide tributyltin.
A 16-HETE in which the chiral centre at position 16 has R-configuration.
